                    {CRW}
                    s cannot accommodate the multiscale autocorrelations that typify modern, finely sampled relocation data sets.
                  
                
                
                  
                    Recent developments in modelling movement as a continuous‐time stochastic process (
                    {CTSP}
                    ) solve these problems, but the mathematical difficulty of using
                    {CTSP}
                    s has limited their adoption in ecology. To remove this roadblock, we introduce the
                    ctmm
